<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-23T01:07:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-23T01:07:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">345.1121 Benz, Heinrich/13:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Calcutta</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calcutta</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-23T12:00:00+05:53">December 23, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 24—8
                                    a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Reference the Department’s telegram of October 4, 8 p.m. The
                                Government of India has announced that it will release Benz for
                                repatriation. As Benz is understood to be practically destitute can
                                the Department arrange with American Export Line through Maritime
                                Commission for his transportation from Calcutta at nominal rate?
                                Please refer to despatch No. 147 dated November 15, 1940, from
                                American Consul at Bombay.<note n="6" xml:id="d145fn6">Not found in
                                    Department files.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>